In a major win for shareholders, a federal judge allowed a class-action lawsuit against Tyco International Ltd. and former executives accused of stealing millions.
The retrial of L. Dennis Kozlowski and Mark Swartz in New York involves charges of grand larceny and fraud.
Prosecutors highlight lavish spending, including a $6,000 shower curtain, to portray greed.
The defense argues that the accusations are part of a self-serving strategy by directors.
The trial's focus shifts to illegal bonuses and concealment from the company's board.
Defense lawyers attack the credibility of former Tyco directors, aiming to sway the jury.
